 <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kitsunenokuyamu@polykarbonbbs>Kitsune no Kuyamu</A> at: 4/27/03 8:16:15 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ascendedbob>Ascended Bob</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(4/26/03 2:19:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=982.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re:I have a story in need of being flamed.</span><hr size=1> Its a pretty good plot so far. The pacing is a little jumpy though. Thats what jumps out to me the most. You manage to be pretty descriptive of the box yet not so much for other things. Still that is all relative to the feeling you wish to evoke. It seems like it should be a fantasy kind of story with a bit of mystery in that box. Yet if you let the story move too fast you'll lose the mystery completely. If I might make a suggestion, I know its kind of boring as a writer in fact I hate doing it myself, give a little more description of the way the character looks. More importantly, in that part where he shoots that silencing gaze to the person, I didn't think he was that kind of person. He just didn't give that presiding/authorative feeling when he sat in the corner and ignored everyone. You could of course leave that part out.<br>
<br>
Anyway its a good start and I have to admit I am curious as to that box. Keep writing.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kitsunenokuyamu@polykarbonbbs>Kitsune no Kuyamu</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Pre-Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(4/26/03 3:31:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=982.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Re:I have a story in need of being flamed.</span><hr size=1> the irony is in the fact that that's exactly what i was told to avoid. i have a tendency to over develop my descriptions, but it looks like i still need to work on a balance. thanks for the input. i'll keep it in mind. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=emmapeel1601>emmapeel1601</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.geocities.com/garaigh/emma2.txt" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(5/6/03 7:45:00 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=982.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/garaigh/buddy2.txt height=127 width=107></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> car rides and visions</span><hr size=1> this is a very interesting idea you're working with. i agree with AscendedBob. the pacing is jumpy. in fact the whole thing seems rushed and i think if you deal with that the balance between description and action. <br>
<br>
what you have so far could be easily drawn out into several pages if not a whole chapter. start with Kitsune sitting in his room staring at the wall and waiting to leave or getting dressed for the occasion. actually show us the argument with his father. what kind of homework is he doing? what kind of music does he listen to? what is his mom like? why is he so intimidating? <br>
<br>
chapter one is the place to set up your character, who he is, how he interacts with other people, etc. the beginning of a story is always the place to lay out the framework for how a character will react and grow later in the story. <br>
<br>
personally i think you should move the bit where he has the vision of the priests to after he gets back in the car. and i would make it longer and more nightmarish to foreshadow the danger of opening the box. <br>
<br>
so, just a few suggestions. keep up the good work! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
